  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="NA50-kiḷavi">itu tōḻi pāṇaṟku vāyiṉ maṟuttatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante refused the door to the bard.</p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="NA50">
<l>            aṟiyā maiyi ṉaṉṉai yañcik</l>
<l>            kuḻaiyaṉ kōtaiyaṉ kuṟumpain toṭiyaṉ</l>
<l>            viḻavayar tuṇaṅkai taḻūukañ cella</l>
<l>            neṭunimir teruviṟ kaipuku koṭumiṭai</l>
<l>            notuma lāḷaṉ katumeṉat tākkaliṟ </l>
<l>            kēṭpō ruḷarko lillaikol pōṟṟeṉa</l>
<l>            yāṇṭaiya pacalai yeṉṟaṉa ṉataṉetir</l>
<l>            nāṇilai yeluva veṉṟuvan ticiṉē</l>
<l>            ceṟunarum viḻaiyuñ cemma lōṉeṉa</l>
<l>            naṟunuta larivai pōṟṟeṉ </l>
<l>            ciṟumai perumaiyiṟ kāṇātu tuṇintē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent2">Fearing mother for [her] not knowing,</l>
<l>we didn't go to embrace [him] in the Tuṇaṅkai danced at the festival,</l>
<l rend="indent3">him with earrings, a garland [and] small green[-golden] bracelets.</l>
<l rend="indent">When, as suddenly(?) a stranger assaulted [us] </l>
<l rend="indent3">in the bent within reach of the long straight(?) street,</l>
<l rend="indent">I said “is there anyone who listens? is there not? protect [me]!”,</l>
<l>he said: “from whence [these fits of] pallor?” In reply to that</l>
<l rend="indent3">I came [away] with “you have no shame, friend.”</l>
<l>I won't spare [him], oh young woman with fragrant forehead,</l>
<l rend="indent2">saying “he [is] a superior one whom even [his] enemies respect”,</l>
<l>resolving that [his] smallness is not seen in [his] greatness.<note place="foot">The fine point in this poem of indirect messages seems to be that HE made avances to the confidante at a time when SHE was not available, and it is the confidante's intention to let HER know the facts.</note></l>
        </lg>
         </div>
